The primary cause for the historical psychological idiom (the glass delusion) shifting to incorporate modern industrial and scientific advancements was the **decline of glass as a culturally novel and metaphorically potent symbol**, combined with the emergence of new technologies that provided fresh idioms for expressing distress. 

